[1] OIE report
Date: Wed 3 Oct 2012
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2012; 25(40) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=12394


Equine infectious anemia, United Kingdom
----------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 3 Oct 2012 from Dr Nigel Gibbens, Chief Veterinary Officer, Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, LONDON, United Kingdom

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 22 Sep 2012
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 3 Oct 2012
Report date: 3 Oct 2012
Date submitted to OIE: 3 Oct 2012
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 21 Dec 2010
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Equine infectious anemia virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak Location: England (Cornwall)
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 26 / 1 / 0 / 1 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: equine infectious anemia was confirmed on 3 Oct 2012 in a 10-year-old gelding based on positive results obtained on the AGID (Coggin's test). Samples were collected following clinical signs of anemia. 25 in-contact horses have been restricted and samples taken. Initial results are negative with some results still pending. An epidemiological inquiry is currently under way.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods; stamping out; movement control inside the country; screening; zoning; dipping/spraying; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Animal Health and Veterinary Laboratories Agency (AHVLA), Weybridge (regional reference laboratory)
Tests and results
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Equidae / [AGID] / 3 Oct 2012 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

